      </FaqItem>
      <FaqItem question="How long should grinding one dose take?">
        <p>With a solid steel-burr manual grinder, 18g usually takes around 30 to 55 seconds for filter ranges and 40 to 75 seconds for espresso-fine settings.</p>
      </FaqItem>
      <FaqItem question="Do ceramic burr hand grinders still make sense?">
        <p>They can, especially for travel and low budgets, but they are usually slower and less precise than steel-burr alternatives. For daily consistency, steel is generally the stronger choice.</p>
      </FaqItem>
      <FaqItem question="How often should I clean a manual coffee grinder?">
        <p>Brush out loose grounds every few days and deep-clean burrs every 3 to 5 weeks. Frequent cleaning helps keep grind output stable and reduces stale flavor carryover.</p>
